{CHARACTER_NAME}: CAROLYN
{DIALOGUE}: I will sell this house today.
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: She neatly arranges her sales materials on a desk, then strips down to her undergarments.
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: MONTAGE:
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: We see Carolyn, working with fierce concentration as she:
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: Cleans glass doors that overlook the patio and pool;
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: Doggedly scrubs countertops in the kitchen;
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: Perches on a stepladder to dust a cheap-looking ceiling fan in the master bedroom;
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: And vacuums a dirty carpet that will never be clean.
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: Throughout all this, she keeps repeating to herself:
