{DIALOGUE}: We are splitting up.
{CHARACTER_NAME}: CAROLYN
{DIALOGUE}: Buddy.
{DIALOGUE}: I'm so sorry.
{CHARACTER_NAME}: BUDDY
{META_DATA}: (bitterly)
{DIALOGUE}: Yes, according to her, I'm too focused on my career.
{DIALOGUE}: As if being driven to succeed is some sort of character flaw.
{DIALOGUE}: Well, she certainly knew how to take advantage of the lifestyle my success afforded her.
{DIALOGUE}: Oh.
{DIALOGUE}: Wow.
{META_DATA}: (then, laughing)
{DIALOGUE}: Ah, it's for the best.
{META_DATA}: (CONTINUED)
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: 52.
{META_DATA}: CONTINUED:
{CHARACTER_NAME}: CAROLYN
{DIALOGUE}: When I saw you two at the party the other night, you seemed perfectly happy.
{CHARACTER_NAME}: BUDDY
{DIALOGUE}: Well, call me crazy, but it is my philosophy that in order to be successful, one must project an image of success, at all times.
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: He smiles, then opens his menu.
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: Carolyn picks hers up mechanically, but continues to stare at him, enraptured, like a fervent Christian who's just come face to face with Jesus.
{SCENE_BOUNDARY}: EXT. HIGH SCHOOL CAMPUS - LATER THAT DAY
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: Ricky stands with his DIGICAM, videotaping something on the ground at his feet.
